      <h2>Description:</h2>
      <p>Storing energy is a great way of using energy when it is available and then using it later on. For example it can be useful for power cuts as it allows time for everything to be powered down to avoid any electrical damage. Energy can be stored in a variety of ways. The most common being electric batteries, heat batteries and thermal stores.<br>
        The electric batteries can help make the most out of the renewable energy. For example solar panel only work in the day but there is a lot of excess energy that gets sold back to the grid. If this energy could be used to charge a battery then energy can be provided during the night as well.<br>
        Heat batteries are used to store spare heat or electricity. The energy is stored in a material as it changes phases from a solid to a liquid. When the heat is needed the material changes back into a solid and release the heat which is used to provide hot water.<br>
        Thermal stores are where excess energy is used to heat up water and is stored in an insulated tank which can be used to provide hot water.
      </p>
